You&#39;re confusing `indexOf`, which [is a `method` on the `string prototype`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String/indexOf), with directory indexes, which are completely unrelated.

As-is, there is nothing in the JS that you posted that will prevent you from using it with external stylesheets. In fact, here is an example I threw together that shows it being used two externally hosted stylesheets:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: false babel: false --&gt;

