It looks like a bug when we do a fallback to SpEL invocation and it just can&#39;t find a method with expected argument type to call. Please, raise an issue against [Spring Integration][1]. We have the same problem even with regular Java, not only Kotlin.

As a workaround I&#39;d suggest to use a `filter()` instead of `transform()` since a `PayloadMethodArgumentResolver` for an `InvocableHandlerMethod` doesn&#39;t allow an *empty payload* by default:

    if (isEmptyPayload(payload)) {
			if (ann == null || ann.required()) {
				String paramName = getParameterName(parameter);
				BindingResult bindingResult = new BeanPropertyBindingResult(payload, paramName);
				bindingResult.addError(new ObjectError(paramName, &quot;Payload value must not be empty&quot;));
				throw new MethodArgumentNotValidException(message, parameter, bindingResult);
			}

**UPDATE**

I went ahead and created an issue: https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-integration/issues/3079

